Arabidopsis_enrich_gene_visualization

1 Introduction

This is a Notebook for enrichment ratio results visualization. The output from a custom python script shows: 1. Target genomic feature density surround real breakpoints; 2. Target genomic feature density surround 10,000 (default number) pseudo breakpoints, with 1,000 (default number) random selective pseudo population; 3. One t-test results displaying the p-value with each pseudo population and the real breakpoints group.

This R script is aimed to visualize these data into density plot, by using ggplot package.

4 histogram with density plot with mean line

gene.den.meanline.1k <- ggplot(df.random.1k, aes(x=Mean.1k)) +
  geom_histogram(colour="black", fill="black", bins = 120) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=realmean.1k, color="blue"), size=2, show.legend = FALSE) +
  scale_x_continuous(name = "Mean gene density") +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Number of Breakpoints") +
  labs(title = "Gene density in 1kb window") +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 10), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12), plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5))
gene.den.meanline.1k

5 draw text for p-value and ratio info

text1 <- paste("Enrichment Ratio = 0.41\nP-value = 1.08E-4***")
text1.p <- ggparagraph(text = text1, color = "black", size = 8)

6 add statistical info to plot

den.text.1k <- CT9.den.meanline.1k + annotation_custom(ggplotGrob(text1.p),xmin = 0.01, xmax = 0.2, ymax = 40)
den.text.1k
